title: Magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes off southern Philippines
text:
Magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes off southern Philippines

Global 1 hour ago (Sep 29, 2019 12:00)

Magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes off southern Philippines MANILA, Sept 29 (Reuters) - A magnitude 6.4 earthquake

struck off the province of Davao Occidental in the southern

Philippines on Sunday morning, the Philippine Institute of

Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said.

There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage but

several aftershocks were felt, Phivolcs said in its advisory.

The epicentre was 126 km (78 miles) southeast of Jose Abad

Santos town.
